# UI Components & Styling

SciWeb 3.0 uses a consistent UI system with reusable components and CSS variables for theming.

## Styling Architecture

- **CSS Variables:** Defined in [static/css/style.css](mdc:static/css/style.css) with a root scope
- **Page-specific CSS:** Each major page has its own CSS file (login.css, profile.css, etc.)
- **Responsive Design:** Media queries for different viewport sizes
- **Dark/Light Mode:** Theme toggle in the navbar with `.dark-mode` class controlling appearance

## Color Scheme

```css
:root {
  --primary: #ff1a75;
  --primary-light: #ff4d94;
  --primary-dark: #cc0051;
  --secondary: #3e3e3e;
  --text-light: #f5f5f5;
  --text-dark: #212121;
  --bg-light: #ffffff;
  --bg-dark: #121212;
  --bg-light-accent: #f0f0f0;
  --bg-dark-accent: #1e1e1e;
}
```

## Common Components

### Buttons

Three main button types:
- `.btn-primary` - Main action buttons in primary color
- `.btn-secondary` - Secondary actions
- `.btn-danger` - Destructive actions

```html
<button class="btn btn-primary">Primary Action</button>
<button class="btn btn-secondary">Secondary Action</button>
<button class="btn btn-danger">Danger Action</button>
```

### Form Elements

Standard form components:
- Text inputs
- Password fields with toggle visibility
- Radio buttons
- Checkboxes
- Dropdowns

```html
<div class="form-group">
    <label for="field-id">Field Label</label>
    <input type="text" id="field-id" class="form-control">
</div>
```

### Cards

Card components for content containers:
- Login/signup cards
- Feature cards
- Content cards

```html
<div class="card">
    <div class="card-header">Card Title</div>
    <div class="card-body">Card content goes here</div>
    <div class="card-footer">Card footer</div>
</div>
```

### Navigation

- Main navbar in [templates/base.html](mdc:templates/base.html)
- Tab navigation patterns used in profile page

